{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make time spent on other work visa categories to count towards ILR in 5 years",
        "additional_details": "Foreign workers are generally not aware of various visa routes. They enter the UK based on opportunity offered by employer, subject to available sponsor license/CoS\r\n\r\nThese workers contribute to economy similar to those in skilled worker route. Current policies on some routes e.g. ICT do not allow time spent in the UK to be counted for ILR in 5 years\r\n\r\nGovernment should review current policies on ILR after 5 years for all work visa routes and set an example of fair treatment to all foreign workers",
        "background": "There are multiple work visa routes allowing workers to come in the UK. Few of these routes do not offer settlement after 5 years e.g. ICT visa holders, even if workers pay appropriate taxes. Government should treat all foreign workers equally and offer similar settlement options",
